"&#xa0;\nWritten evidence submitted by Wienerberger Ltd&#xa0;INTRODUCTION&#xa0;\n&#xa0;DETAILED COMMENTS&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;CONCLUSIONS&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n20 \nOctober 2013\n&#xa0;Declaration of interests.Wienerberger\n AG is the world’s largest producer of clay bricks and number 1 in clay roof tiles in Europe with 230 factories in 30 countries. Most of these are situated in EU Member States but some are outside the EU including the USA and India. The Group Head Office is based in Vienna.\n&#xa0;\nWienerberger\n Ltd in the UK – including the sister Company \nSandtoft\n Roof Tiles Ltd – have a total of 14 manufacturing sites and a current workforce of around 1,000. Only 13 of these sites are currently operational.\n The Company manufactures clay facing and engineering bricks, clay pavers and roof tiles manufactured in clay, concrete and reconstituted slate.\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"